        {
            "+content": "No one in Amigasa questions the government's rule over their lives, except for Dante. Dyslexic and unable to read, Dante spends his time among the soldiers of Amigasa wondering what may lie outside, and why he's not allowed to go see. When he finally gets his wish, a chance meeting with a girl named Aoi sets him on a path of direct opposition to the government of Amigasa. Dante may find himself embroiled in an ever-escalating conspiracy he can't fully understand, but his offbeat approach to the situation may be the missing component the rebels were needing all this time. <em class=de-emphasized>(from manga)</em>",
